 
<p>
  Deep-sea mining is <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2022/jul/08/nowhere-is-free-from-noise-deep-sea-mining-threat-to-marine-mammals">noisy, and the noise can travel for hundreds of
  miles in water</a>.  It can interfere with marine animals' reproduction
  or safety, and thus disrupt ecosystems.

 